  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "couName": "VAD use",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Higher model risk drives stricter credibility requirements; Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed but all credibility factor gaps remain. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all with achieved levels below required levels), 6 factors not assessed (flagged as epistemic gaps at MRL 5). Decision: Not accepted. A screening sensitivity study was conducted to rank the relative influence of inlet boundary conditions, viscosity model parameters, and mesh density on the hemolysis index; however this screening exercise is documented only in the narrative and has not been elevated to a formal structured sensitivity analysis node within this credibility package.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Low",
  "decision": "Not accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class III",
  "modelRiskLevel": 5,
